config.prompt_template:
You are a CPG analyst writing a morning briefing for {{ user_id }}.
Time of day: {{ user_state.get('time_bucket', 'morning') }}.
Since last visit ({{ user_state.get('last_visited_at', 'never') }}), here are the changes:

Recent sales:
{% for row in dsp_data %}- {{ row.d }}: {{ row.region }} region ${{ row.rev | int }}
{% endfor %}

Related news:
{% for n in external_info %}- {{ n.title }} — {{ n.url }}
{% endfor %}

Return a JSON object with keys: narrative_text (markdown, max 120 words), key_points (array of 2-4 bullets), suggested_actions (array of 0-3 imperative short sentences).

Analyze the following weekly sell-through data. Identify SKUs with sell-through < 20% (slow movers) or > 80% (fast movers at risk of stockout). For each flagged category, suggest actions (replenishment, promotion, clearance).

Sell-Through Data:
{% for row in dsp_data %}
- {{ row.sku }} ({{ row.category }}): {{ row.sell_through_pct }}% sell-through, {{ row.units_sold }} units, {{ row.avg_inventory }} avg inventory
{% endfor %}

Return a JSON object with: narrative_text (markdown summary), slow_movers (array of SKU objects with sku, reason), fast_movers (array of SKU objects with sku, reason).

Rank the following SKUs by stockout urgency. A SKU is urgent if days_of_cover < 3 or if daily demand exceeds current stock. For each SKU, assign a score (0-100, higher = more urgent) and provide a brief reason.

Candidates:
{% for row in dsp_data %}
- {{ row.sku }} ({{ row.category }}): {{ row.days_of_cover }} days of cover, {{ row.projected_daily_demand }} daily demand
{% endfor %}

Return a JSON array of items, each with: id (sku), rank (1-10), score (0-100), reason (text).

Explain the price change anomaly detected for this product. Consider: regional market conditions, competitive prices, cost inflation, promotion context, and seasonal patterns.

Price Change:
- SKU: {{ dsp_data[0].sku if dsp_data else 'unknown' }}
- Region: {{ dsp_data[0].region if dsp_data else 'unknown' }}
- Previous Price: ${{ dsp_data[0].previous_price if dsp_data else 'N/A' }}
- Current Price: ${{ dsp_data[0].current_price if dsp_data else 'N/A' }}
- Change: {{ dsp_data[0].price_delta_pct if dsp_data else 'N/A' }}%
- Changed on: {{ dsp_data[0].price_change_date if dsp_data else 'N/A' }}

Return a JSON object with: label (text for button label), explanation_text (detailed explanation in 2-3 sentences).

Analyze the promotional lift results. For each campaign, summarize the revenue and unit lift, identify top-performing SKUs, and comment on campaign effectiveness.

Promo Results:
{% for row in dsp_data %}
- {{ row.campaign_name }} ({{ row.start_date }} to {{ row.end_date }}): +${{ row.revenue_lift | int }} revenue, +{{ row.unit_lift | int }} units ({{ row.skus_in_promo }} SKUs)
{% endfor %}

Return a JSON object with: narrative_text (markdown summary of overall performance and insights, max 150 words).

Rank the top 5 KPIs that need management attention per category. Consider: revenue trend, margin erosion, return rate anomalies, unit volume changes. For each category, identify which 1-2 metrics require immediate action.

Category Metrics (30-day):
{% for row in dsp_data %}
- {{ row.category }}: ${{ row.revenue | int }} revenue, {{ row.margin | round(1) }}% margin, {{ row.units | int }} units, {{ row.return_rate | round(1) }}% returns
{% endfor %}

Return a JSON array where each item is: {category, priority_kpi_1, priority_kpi_2, score (0-100), action_text}.

Evaluate supplier performance across reliability, quality, and speed. For each supplier, assess health status (green/yellow/red) and recommend actions: continue, conditional review, or escalation.

Supplier Metrics (30-day):
{% for row in dsp_data %}
- {{ row.supplier_name }}: {{ row.otd }}% on-time, {{ row.quality }} quality score, {{ row.lead_time }} day lead time, {{ row.order_count }} orders
{% endfor %}

Return a JSON object with: narrative_text (summary of supplier ecosystem health and 1-2 recommended actions).

Enhance the SKU master data by enriching the product title, description, and tags. Use category, ingredients, weight, and attributes to generate: a richer product title (max 80 chars), a detailed description emphasizing benefits and use cases (max 300 chars), and 3-5 relevant tags.

Current Data:
{% for row in dsp_data %}
- SKU {{ row.sku }} ({{ row.category }})
  Title: {{ row.current_title }}
  Desc: {{ row.current_description }}
  Ingredients: {{ row.ingredients }}
  Size: {{ row.net_weight }} {{ row.uom }}
{% endfor %}

Return a JSON array where each item has: sku, title_suggested, description_suggested, tags (array of strings).
